modules.description: Provides functions to define and manage command-line interfaces using a declarative approach, with support for configuring options, commands, and their relationships. Works with custom data types representing configurations, options, and command structures. Enables creation of extensible CLIs by inheriting and modifying existing configurations.

Provides functions to define and parse command-line interfaces with object-oriented principles, including method registration and argument handling. Works with classes that encapsulate command logic, options, and subcommands. Used to build structured CLI tools with hierarchical command organization and type-safe input processing.
